## **Recommended Package Structure for Multiple Screens:**

### **1. Navigation Structure**
```kotlin
// com/match/core/navigation/Routes.kt
@Serializable
sealed interface Routes {
 @Serializable data object MatchmateHome : Routes
 @Serializable data class Profile(val userId: String) : Routes
 @Serializable data class Chat(val matchId: String) : Routes
 @Serializable data object Settings : Routes
 @Serializable data object Login : Routes
}

// com/match/core/navigation/NavigationEvent.kt
sealed interface NavigationEvent {
 data object NavigateBack : NavigationEvent
 data class NavigateToRoute(val route: Routes) : NavigationEvent
 data class ShowSnackbar(val message: String) : NavigationEvent
}
```

### **2. Feature-Based Structure**
```
com.match/
 core/
 navigation/ # App-wide navigation
 Routes.kt
 NavigationEvent.kt
 AppNavigation.kt
 ui/
 components/ # Shared UI components
 theme/
 utils/
 feature/
 auth/ # Authentication feature
 presentation/
 login/
 LoginScreen.kt
 LoginViewModel.kt
 LoginState.kt
 LoginAction.kt
 register/
 domain/
 data/
 matchmate/ # Main matching feature
 presentation/
 home/ # Current MatchmateScreen
 profile/ # User profiles
 swipe/ # Swiping cards
 domain/
 data/
 chat/ # Chat feature
 presentation/
 list/ # Chat list
 detail/ # Individual chat
 domain/
 data/
 settings/ # App settings
 presentation/
 domain/
 data/
 MainActivity.kt
```

### **3. Benefits of This Structure:**

#### **Scalability**
- Each feature is self-contained
- Easy to add new features
- Clear separation of concerns

#### **Navigation Management**
- Centralized route definitions
- Type-safe navigation
- Single source of truth for navigation events

#### **Team Collaboration**
- Different developers can work on different features
- Minimal merge conflicts
- Clear ownership boundaries

#### **Testing**
- Each feature can be tested independently
- Clear dependency boundaries
- Easy to mock dependencies

### **4. How Navigation Works Across Features:**

```kotlin
// Any ViewModel in any feature can emit navigation events
class ProfileViewModel : ViewModel() {
 fun onChatClicked(matchId: String) {
 _event.trySend(NavigationEvent.NavigateToRoute(Routes.Chat(matchId)))
 }
}

// MainActivity handles all navigation centrally
@Composable
fun AppNavigation() {
 NavHost(...) {
 composable<Routes.MatchmateHome> {
 MatchMateRoot(onEvent = handleNavigationEvent)
 }
 composable<Routes.Profile> {
 ProfileRoot(onEvent = handleNavigationEvent)
 }
 composable<Routes.Chat> {
 ChatRoot(onEvent = handleNavigationEvent)
 }
 }
}
```

### **5. Migration Strategy:**

For your current code, I'd recommend:

1. **Phase 1**: Keep current structure, add navigation
2. **Phase 2**: Create `core/navigation` package
3. **Phase 3**: Gradually move features to `feature/` structure
4. **Phase 4**: Organize screens within features

